Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.67,0:00:09.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's Theo Cornaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.80,0:00:11.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's much younger than I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.30,0:00:17.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To launch an attack on Ladvan Torius' castle,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.89,0:00:20.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we'll first need to\Nsuccessfully capture that town.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.31,0:00:25.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If a battle ensues, both sides are\Nsure to see heavy casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.57,0:00:31.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That youth is the one\Nwho defeated the Waldlind knights?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.03,0:00:33.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What will become of our town?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.24,0:00:38.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It would be better to avoid a battle, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.79,0:00:44.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But their leader, Lord Ladvan,\Nis a man of conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.17,0:00:46.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what you propose,\NI'm sure he won't surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.96,0:00:49.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But Sir Theo, maybe you can...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.43,0:00:55.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now this is just the next-best plan...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.05,0:01:00.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If he refuses to surrender, please convince\Nhim to settle things outside the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.52,0:01:04.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As a man who values his people,\NI'm sure he'll comply.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.79,0:02:51.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am the leader of this village, Ladvan Torius!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.01,0:02:58.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am a knight serving Villar Constance,\Nthe Earl of Artuk...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.18,0:03:00.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Theo Cornaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.09,0:03:05.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've agreed to meet with you,\Nbut my mind is already made up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.27,0:03:10.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If it's my court rank and land you desire,\NI will take you on, but only in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.27,0:03:14.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you're swearing\Nallegiance to the Alliance?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.48,0:03:19.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I plan to offer Lady Marrine Kreische\Nmy pledge of fealty down the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.61,0:03:21.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.57,0:03:24.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With so many townspeople here to defend you,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.99,0:03:27.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have no hope of defeating you\Nwith my troops alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.87,0:03:30.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I do not wish to harm your people in a battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.67,0:03:35.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can see why you're renowned as a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.09,0:03:37.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I advise you to leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.34,0:03:39.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's my intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.18,0:03:42.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But before I go,\NI have one question for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.60,0:03:46.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the victory that you seek?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.68,0:03:49.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That should be more than obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.60,0:03:53.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sooner or later, the great Union army\Nwill arrive to attack this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.19,0:03:56.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was able to survive this long.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.40,0:04:00.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I withdraw,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.82,0:04:04.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lassic David, the King of Sievis,\Nis sure to attack with his force of 30,000 men.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.99,0:04:05.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,30,000?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.37,0:04:07.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We wouldn't stand a chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.12,0:04:12.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you wish to become\Nthe true victor in all this,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.17,0:04:15.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suggest that you lead your men\Nfrom the castle to attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.75,0:04:17.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.92,0:04:21.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In doing so, your loyalty to\Nthe Alliance will remain unscathed,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.42,0:04:23.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and your people won't have to suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.76,0:04:30.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I can go down holding my own\Nagainst the hero Theo Cornaro,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.02,0:04:31.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will die a happy man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.94,0:04:35.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to die as a victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.65,0:04:37.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, that won't do!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.07,0:04:40.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We are prepared to fight\Nby your side, Lord Ladvan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.40,0:04:42.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, everybody?\NIsn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.49,0:04:44.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right! That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.54,0:04:52.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I die, this battle will come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.66,0:04:55.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need for you to sacrifice your lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.59,0:05:01.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Ladvan...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.22,0:05:06.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What we want is for you\Nto continue ruling this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.43,0:05:10.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll follow you wherever you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.10,0:05:12.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who cares if we're with\Nthe Alliance or the Union?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.02,0:05:14.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We will protect you, Lord Ladvan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.69,0:05:15.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Ladvan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.77,0:05:18.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our leader!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.57,0:05:22.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like I've lost here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.86,0:05:28.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're every inch the valiant Lord\NI thought you'd be.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.16,0:05:29.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that's why I'd like to ask you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.12,0:05:33.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Would you consider joining me in defeat?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.87,0:05:35.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Join you in defeat?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.54,0:05:40.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking you to value your people's trust,\Nrather than your loyalty to the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.88,0:05:44.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You mean I should be true to my people,\Nrather than be their Lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.80,0:05:48.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's precisely what I see as the ideal Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.65,0:06:07.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, I must ask for your forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.91,0:06:12.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I intend to leave the Alliance,\Nand switch sides to the Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.99,0:06:16.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I choose to live my life alongside all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.72,0:06:30.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I leave my fate entirely in your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.76,0:06:34.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All I ask is that you guarantee\Nmy people's survival and their fortunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.31,0:06:36.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.14,0:06:40.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure Sir Lassic\Nwill give you a warm welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.77,0:06:44.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How unfortunate for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.40,0:06:48.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only I'd vacated my castle,\Nit would've been such a coup for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.11,0:06:50.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and you could've taken my Crest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.66,0:06:53.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care for military feats.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.04,0:06:57.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What matters is that there were\Nno senseless casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.75,0:07:05.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I had the wrong read on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.05,0:07:09.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So many Lords obsess only\Nabout gaining more land or Crests,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.68,0:07:13.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,yet you show concern for not only\Nyour own people, but your enemy's as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.26,0:07:17.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can see that you're a man\Nwho truly adheres to the code of Lords.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.93,0:07:22.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than Lord Lassic,\NI would like to serve under you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.02,0:07:29.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am currently a man serving under Lord Villar.\NI cannot accept your pledge of allegiance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.53,0:07:34.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then, until the time comes,\Nwill you entrust your Crest to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.54,0:07:38.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.91,0:07:43.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be sure to welcome you as a loyal Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.89,0:07:54.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.93,0:07:58.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind surrendering,\Nhe actually promised to serve him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.80,0:08:31.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Lassic has defeated Jericho Orlick,\Nthe King of Forbes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.47,0:08:35.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who knew he'd only take\Nfive days to conquer Forbes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.47,0:08:40.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to him, the King of Clovis\Nsurrendered his castle without any prodding.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.73,0:08:44.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Without us losing a single soldier, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.98,0:08:52.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe both Sir Milza and Sir Theo's exploits\Nhave shattered the enemy's morale.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.95,0:08:55.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Both feats were extraordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.24,0:08:58.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And both were carried out true to form,\Nwouldn't you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.42,0:09:09.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Glory to the Union!\NLord Villar, Earl of Artuk!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.97,0:09:22.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The road to Jalucia has been paved!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.98,0:09:25.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thank you all for your hard work!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.19,0:09:37.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After declining his request for aid,\NI knew this might happen, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.03,0:09:40.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Theo Cornaro, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.45,0:09:46.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milza Kuces didn't even need a day to seize\Nthe castle of one of our more dominant Lords.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.08,0:09:47.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milza?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.71,0:09:51.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't he the son of the Viceroy of Dartania?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.05,0:09:54.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So how are our Lords taking all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.55,0:09:56.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Many of them are distraught.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.39,0:09:58.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.30,0:10:03.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With Sievis lost, and not knowing how\Nthe neighboring Lords will react,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.56,0:10:06.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Waldlind can ill afford to send backup troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.23,0:10:10.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, I'm sure that some\Nwill criticize what I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.82,0:10:14.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Keep your eyes on those Lords!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.07,0:10:17.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.84,0:10:34.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Out of place, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.34,0:10:35.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Out of place, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.34,0:10:38.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder where Lord Alexis is?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.59,0:10:40.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think he'll dance with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.22,0:10:42.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Earl of Artuk, is that you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.98,0:10:48.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's the Earl of Le Couleurs,\NLord Klute Gallas.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.98,0:10:51.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You took so long to show up, I was worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.73,0:10:53.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, our path here was blocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.98,0:10:57.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, we would've given you\Na proper hero's welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.32,0:11:01.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But some of the Lords here\Naren't thrilled with what you've accomplished.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.24,0:11:08.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, my cousin seems to be set on\Ntaking out the Union with military might.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.75,0:11:16.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we must not give Marrine\Nample time to do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.76,0:11:20.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we advance into the Alliance at full strength,\Nand conquer Waldlind,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.64,0:11:23.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we can finish them off for good!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.68,0:11:27.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's the spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.23,0:11:31.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a long time, Marquis Dawson.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.77,0:11:34.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I commend you for your prowess in battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.02,0:11:37.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but didn't I notify you about\Nsuspending hostilities with the Alliance?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.28,0:11:40.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you follow the consensus?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.91,0:11:42.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you're calling it a consensus,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.66,0:11:46.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then you should've\Nconsulted me before sending it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.20,0:11:51.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning you'll go along with whatever\Nis decided at this Lords' Congress, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.42,0:11:54.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure I'll have no other choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.09,0:11:56.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.92,0:11:58.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,don't forget the words you just uttered!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.30,0:12:10.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do most of the Lords here actually believe\Nthat the current peace will last forever?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.31,0:12:11.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.94,0:12:14.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since that battle against\Nthe Alliance thirty years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.56,0:12:18.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,only Artuk and its surrounding areas\Nhave seen battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.69,0:12:22.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that's why this conference\Nis a once-in-a-lifetime chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.74,0:12:23.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Villar, Earl of Artuk!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.91,0:12:26.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tell them what a threat the Alliance is,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.62,0:12:30.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and that to survive, our only option\Nis to mount a full-scale war!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.29,0:12:34.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is not going to be\Na tranquil meeting for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.63,0:12:37.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Marquis of Jalucia, Lord Alexis...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.75,0:12:38.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Entering!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.11,0:13:04.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Villar!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.91,0:13:07.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much\Nfor making the long trip here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.54,0:13:09.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.74,0:13:15.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I would cross the entire continent\Nif it meant getting an audience with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.13,0:13:18.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.71,0:13:24.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You saved me from peril\Nin the Great Hall. I thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.51,0:13:28.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please forgive me for failing\Nto save both archdukes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.76,0:13:30.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.52,0:13:32.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you Sir Theo?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.14,0:13:36.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's an honor to meet you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.02,0:13:38.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.02,0:13:40.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've been wanting to have a nice,\Nlong chat with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.32,0:13:45.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Since it's not possible to do that here,\Nallow me to arrange a meeting sometime!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.86,0:13:47.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not worthy of your kind words, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.57,0:13:49.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Though it's probably lip-service.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.67,0:14:01.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Theo? Siluca?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.67,0:14:02.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.63,0:14:06.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've spotted someone I must introduce you to.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.76,0:14:10.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't seen you\Nsince the last Lords' Congress...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.43,0:14:13.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Pederico Rossini!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.56,0:14:16.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well, the Earl of Artuk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.65,0:14:21.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This young knight here\Nhails from Sistina, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.19,0:14:22.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.82,0:14:29.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My name... is Theo Cornaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.70,0:14:31.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you say Cornaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.91,0:14:36.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Was that name handed down to you\Nby your forebears?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.67,0:14:38.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, I am a commoner.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.75,0:14:43.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When becoming a Lord, I took on a name\Nclosely connected to my homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.67,0:14:46.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Cornaro is a prestigious name in Sistina.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.59,0:14:51.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not to be assumed on a whim\Nby a commoner Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.93,0:14:53.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should take another name.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.77,0:14:55.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't a whim.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.68,0:14:58.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Since I intend to return\Nto my homeland someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.82,0:15:05.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sistina is an island in the demon world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.57,0:15:08.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you go back, no good will come out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.86,0:15:11.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's for me to decide, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.33,0:15:22.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What a day we had, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.63,0:15:24.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.09,0:15:25.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we have some tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.09,0:15:31.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's unusual for Irvin\Nnot to show up at a time like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.72,0:15:36.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we have company.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.56,0:15:39.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Someone of significantly high rank.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.85,0:15:44.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But Lord Villar is still\Nat the Marquis of Jalucia's castle...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.99,0:15:52.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Theo, you have a guest!\NSomeone named Alexis.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.12,0:15:53.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Alexis...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.58,0:15:55.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.50,0:15:59.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's been ordered not to enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.25,0:16:03.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because I wanted to talk to you\Nwith no one else around.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.25,0:16:07.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's an honor, sir.\NBut I'm also perplexed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.34,0:16:11.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're not of sufficient rank\Nto speak with you in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.64,0:16:15.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I only inherited my court rank\Nfrom my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.68,0:16:19.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you, Sir Theo,\Nstrengthened your Crest on your own,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.89,0:16:24.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,became the former ruler of Sievis,\Nand even reached the rank of viscount.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.02,0:16:27.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I certainly didn't\Naccomplish that on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.03,0:16:30.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was all thanks to Siluca here,\Nand my comrades.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.49,0:16:34.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Above all, if Lord Villar hadn't come to my aid,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.12,0:16:35.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't have survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.41,0:16:40.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the court rank and lands\Nyou risked your life to acquire...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.08,0:16:43.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you gave them up for Lady Siluca\Nwithout a second thought?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.63,0:16:48.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was Siluca who guided me\Nwhen I was nothing but a wanderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.55,0:16:51.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it came at the cost of all else,\NI have no regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.43,0:16:56.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I heard that story, I was deeply moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.43,0:16:59.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To choose love over\None's court rank and land...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.06,0:17:02.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only I had the courage to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.44,0:17:06.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All I did was choose\Nwhat was most important to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.78,0:17:12.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In my case, my love for Marrine\Nis more important than anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.49,0:17:15.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I realized that it wasn't meant to be,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.66,0:17:18.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I even considered ending my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.58,0:17:25.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But Marrine has forged a path for\Nus to be united.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.88,0:17:26.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.21,0:17:31.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I still love Marrine, even now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.55,0:17:36.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So much that I'd give up my court rank\Nand lands if it meant we could be together!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.85,0:17:41.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I understand how you feel, but you can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.64,0:17:43.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.27,0:17:48.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Marrine is a woman who\Ntakes her responsibilities seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.48,0:17:52.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure she'll steadfastly try\Nto fulfill her role as leader of the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.03,0:17:57.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hear Lady Marrine still dresses in black\Nand continues to mourn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.41,0:18:00.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure her resolve is ironclad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.87,0:18:07.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My wish is for all Lords across the continent\Nto cease fighting and unite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.25,0:18:10.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then we can hold a meeting\Nto choose our emperor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.50,0:18:14.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That way, there will be\Nno more war on the continent,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.34,0:18:16.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and the era of Chaos will come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.43,0:18:25.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's everything I wanted\Nto talk to you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.02,0:18:29.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And I also want you two to find happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.65,0:18:35.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you can show the world that there are more\Nimportant things than court rank or territories.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.20,0:18:37.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We give you our promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.16,0:18:43.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At present, I am serving the Earl of Artuk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.95,0:18:50.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But aside from that relationship, I will do\Neverything I can to make your wish come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.88,0:18:55.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So that one day,\Nyou and Lady Marrine can be united.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.34,0:18:58.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so the continent will become one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.35,0:19:02.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.81,0:19:12.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When we're not in the public eye,\NI hope you'll think of me as your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.73,0:19:14.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'll be thinking of you as mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.78,0:19:16.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.36,0:19:20.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- I would love to stay, but I must return to...\N- We're under attack
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.07,0:19:21.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, please watch your backs!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.08,0:19:29.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wall, O Wall!\NNothing on this earth can hope to scale it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.10,0:19:49.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Alexis!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.69,0:19:55.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who are these guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.49,0:20:02.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Omerta...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.49,0:20:04.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is Rossini's flag.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.37,0:20:08.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No one who accepts it can go against orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.16,0:20:11.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how cruel the action may be,\Nhe'll carry it out without remorse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.75,0:20:14.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's the enemy after?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.60,0:20:25.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Parry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.36,0:20:36.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.28,0:20:39.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No need to thank me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.87,0:20:51.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Siluca...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.83,0:20:54.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?\NNot being here when we needed you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.17,0:20:56.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.05,0:20:59.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You were being targeted by snipers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.84,0:21:04.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And there was a Shadow among them,\Nholding me back...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.76,0:21:06.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely, it was an assassin.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.64,0:21:07.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you kill it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.72,0:21:09.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It got away from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.44,0:21:17.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You were all exposed to danger because of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.36,0:21:21.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.04,0:21:35.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was the target, wasn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.25,0:21:38.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it was mistaken identity,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.13,0:21:41.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,an assassination attempt on a marquis\Nis far from a minor offense.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.34,0:21:45.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When he finds out\Nthat he got Lord Alexis involved,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.14,0:21:46.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I bet Rossini will be stunned.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.14,0:21:53.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no question that the Rossini clan\Nwill be expelled from the Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.94,0:21:58.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And when that happens,\Nit'll be our turn to make a move.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.03,0:22:05.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,THE WHITE PRINCE
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.04,0:23:40.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,THE CONGRESS DANCES
